embed.title: Staff | Rules
embed.description:
Here are all the staff rules of ***Miami Beach Roleplay** :
### - Duty
 You may **ONLY** start your duty if there are 9+ **REAL** players in-game, also, you **use**, your assigned callsign.
### - Off-Duty and Banned Commands
 You may **NOT** use any commands while being off-duty, even if calls are stacking when there are less than 9 real players, also, you may **NOT** use any restricted commands.
### - Chain of Command
 You **MUST** respect the chain of command and respect the orders of you higher-ups except if they try to make you break rule or if the orders are abusive.
### - SPaG (Spelling, Punctuation and Grammar)
 When on-duty, youu **MUST** always use SPaG whether you're patrolling, answering calls or talking with friends/others staff members.
### - Patrol
 When on-duty, you may **NOT** wait for a call with your car parked, by that, I mean that you must patrol around the map.
### - Respect
 You **MUST** always be disrespectful towards everyone in discord and in-game whether you're off or on-duty.
### - Internals Affairs Investigations
 You may **NOT** interfere with any IA Investigations.
### - 4 letters commands
 When you use a command, you **MUST** use 4 letters commands (usernames), for example, execute :to vava and not :to vav.
### - Help Requests
 When there is an active help request, you **MUST** abandon roleplay and get on-duty, also, you may **ONLY** make an help requests if you are the only staff in-game, on-duty or if calls are stacking.

embed.title: Discord Rules
embed.description:
### •  Rule 1: Respect - Engage in fun conversations, treat everyone with consideration, value their worth, and uphold established guidelines.
### •  Rule 2: Applications - When submitting an application, you are not to talk about, hint, or request for it to be read or accepted. Doing so will result in a denial.
### •  Rule 3: Pinging - Do not Mass Ping anyone, especially staff. Senior High-rank have a Ping Permission role to halt the constant pings.
### •  Rule 4: Channel Use - Every channel has a meaning; all talkable channels also have a meaning. Public-Chat is not a command executor section. You must go to the Bot Commands. Misuse of certain channels may result in Community Warnings or Punishments.
### •  Rule 5: Doxxing - Doxxing, the act of publishing someone’s private information online without their consent, invading their privacy or putting them in danger (which may involve real-life purposes, like leaking age, face, address, full name, Driver’s licence, etc.), is prohibited.
### •  Rule 6: Metagaming - Using a Website, such as Discord, as a way to figure out someone’s in-game movements or plans is Metagaming. Using outside knowledge for Roleplay Purpose is also prohibited.
### •  Rule 7: Confidential - All locked channels are because their purpose is only for certain people to see them. Everything said in that channel is to be only discussed within that channel or the people access to it.
### •  Rule 8: Begging for Roles - You are not to beg for Roles. Staff roles are rightfully earned. Not to be free-ranked given out. Only department roles, Social Media Roles, and Ping Roles are obtainable.
### •  Rule 9: Language - Keep swearing to a minimum and don’t directly focus it to somebody. Racial Slurs or anything beyond too far is deemed prohibited.
### •  Rule 10: Speaking Language - This is an English Only Server. Meaning so, you must only abide by speaking English. Other language is strictly Prohibited as staff may have issues communicating.
